{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn92073203/00332893087/1945112901/0412.xml":{"full_text":"PAGE EIGHT\nWhiskers Tickle\nP l|fr\nUMi^gSPv^&*&\u00a3\u2022 :?&v\nRjflm\u00a3||aagn|\nJIl\nps||ggz\nf \u2019iL'tMoflfflM\u00df\nMaybe it was Santa\u2019s beard that\nilrightened this Philadelphia young\nster upon his first introduction to\n\u2019that amiable old gentleman. It won\u2019t\ntake long, however, for Santa to dis\npel any and all fears.\nScot Private Tells\nHow 6 Silent Night 9\nStilled War Guns\nIt was Christmas Eve, 1914, be\ntween Armentiers and Arras, while\nGordon Highlanders huddled in\ntrenches when somebody remem\nbered the day.\n\"Jim, let\u2019s sing,\u201d one said to Pri\nvate James Sutherland-Watt of Nor\nfolk, Va.\nJim pleaded off, but someone else\nstarted \u201cSilent Night, Holy Night,\u2019\u2019\nand soon Jim and the whole Scot\nregiment had joined in.\nWhen the last refrain subsided,\nfrom the opposite trenches arose\nother voices attuned in \u201cSt,ille\nNacht.\u201d Then all night long Christ\nmas carols rang from trench to\ntrench in strange tongues while can\nnon and flares from other sectors lit\nthe sky.\nAt the customary \u201czero\" hour, the\nBritish soldiers saw gray-clad fig\nures making their way out of the\nopposite trenches. A few shots were\nfired. Then it vfras seen that the\nGermans carried no arms. Scots\nleaped from their trenches, likewise\nunarmed, only to be ordered back.\nReindeer Often Figure in\nNorthern Myth and Legend\nReindeer figure often in northern\nmyth and folklore. In one version of\nthe legend of Way land, the smith,\ntf-ayland and his two brothers leave\nF'ii/'and for the south on their rein\nsleighs. The mountain\nelves try to stop them and Way\nland\u2019s brothers lash their reindeer\nto force them by the elves. Angry\nbecause the three are deserting their\nhomes, but even more because oi\n.the blows given the patient deer, the\nraives curse the two brothers, sing\ning;\n\"Because Slagfid struck bis reindeer\nBecause Eigel struck his reindeer\nOur hatred shall follow you.\u2019\u2019\n\"Wayland they also curse for leav\ning Finland, but because \u201che struck\n1 not his reindeer\u201d the curse is mild\n\u00abr. The two brothers die violent\n\"\u2022and tragically, but Wayland, after\nmany troubles, wins back the wife\nhe had lost and becomes the \u201cSmith\nof the Gods.\u201d\nCave of the Nativity\nNow\u00dfeligiousGrotto\nThe \u201cstable\u201d in which Christ\nwas bom does not conform to the\nmodem conception of the word,\ni In Biblical times, places of\nl shelter were hewn in rocky\n1 ledges; Judean travelers, fre\nquently housed in such caves,\nwelcomed joint tenancy with\nbeasts because of the extra\nwarmth provided by animals\u2019\nbodies.\nThe birthplace of Jesus was\nsuch a cave. Now a grotto be\nneath Bethlehem\u2019s Church of the\nNativity, the entire surface has\nbeen elaborately ornamented. Pil\ngrims to the shrine often wish,\nnonetheless reverently, that its\noriginal simplicity might have\nbeen preserved in which eternal\nstars\n\u201cLooked down where He lay\nThe little Lord Jesus\nAsleep in the hay.\u201d\n\nInfluenced Customs\nThe Germans, perhaps more than\nany other colonists, influenced\nChristmas customs in the United\nStates, which celebrates Christmas\nmore extensively than any other.\nOur concept of Santa Claus is wholly\nfrom Germany, and the Christmas\ntree in'the home is another custom\nthat came over with German emi\ngrants in the last century.\nIn Dance Measure\nChristmas carols were in dance\nmeasure at first. The word carol\ncomes from \"corolla.\u201d a ring, be\ncause the song was for a ring dance.\nOld Custom\nChristmas caroling was a thriving\ncustom in England of the fourth cen\ntury.\nYule Log\nFrom pagan Scandinavian worship\nof Thor comes the Yule log, lighted\nwith a brand from last year\u2019s log\nWELCOME HOME\nVETERANS\nDuring the past week the Ashe\nCounty men listed below have re\nceived honorable discharges from\nMilitary Service, according to records Button Os\nat the Selective Service Office here. Honor\nThe following boys, who have\nreported to the local draft board,\nhave been honorably discharged\nfrom the army during the past\nweek:\nWest Jefferson: Allan Miller,\nWalter E. Phillips, William C.\nMullis, Robert F. McNeill, John\nG. Jackson.\nJefferson: Carl T. Goodman.\nTodd: Franklin P. Trivette.\nGrassy Creek: Ray J. Blevins.\nGlendale Springs: Wayne C.\nTimely Hints\nBy RUTH CURRENT\nTaking care of a man\u2019s suit\nmakes sense any time, but this\nfall brings special reasons for\ncare of suits, new and old, say\nclothing specialists. Suits are\nstill made of wartime fabrics that\nneed help from the wearers to\nkeep them looking well and to\ngive service. Here are a few re\nminders for suit care. Keep suits\nbrushed. Get dust out of folds\nand corners. Work with the\ngrain of the cloth and use a good\nclothes brush. A whisk broom\nonly hits high spots. A suit prop\nerly brushed and hung needs less\npressing.\nHang coats squarely on broad\nwooden hangers of the wishbone\nshape made of men\u2019s suits. When\na coat must hang on a chan*, take\ntime to pull shoulders into shape\nover chair corners. If a coat\nmust hang on a hook, hank it by\nthe loop at the back of the neck.\nBest way to hang trousers is\nupside down, using a hanger\nwith clips. If trousers must be\nlaid over the crossbar of a wire\nhanger, fasten cardboard or thick\npaper over the crossbar, to pre\nvent a sharp crease. Check but\ntons for tightness once in a while.\nIt is still not easy to match iost\nbuttons.\nTrousers finished about <me\nhalf inch above the heels look and\nwear best at the lower edge A\nstrip of cloth or tape sewed just\ninside the edge takes the brunt\nof wear off the trouser cuff.\nFOR ONE OF THE LARGEST ASSORTMENTS OF\nTOYS IN TOWN, COME TO THE\nWestern Auto Asso. Store\nFor The Kiddies\nJust the things for filling\ntheir stockings. Come in and\nsee our selection of toys.\nWorth Knox, Creston\nTrains\nGk that the little boys will want.\nterv Complete sets, reasonably\npriced.\nTeddie Bears\nJust what they will want to\nfind under the tree on Christ- Y\nmas morning.\nNew Plastic Blocks\nFor the ones who haven\u2019t I\n1 started to school. They\u2019ll love\nVi these novel blocks.\nEVERYTHING LITTLE\nGIRLS LOVE\nTea sets, doll houses, dolls,\ndoll beds, minature tele- |l|ip\nphones, table and chair sets.\nSEE OUR ASSORTMENT. YOU\u2019LL WANT TO BUY\nFROM\nWestern Auto Asso. Store\nWest Jefferson, North Carolina\nBare and Don Miller.\nHemlock: Arthur J. Osborne.\nSturgills: Theodore R. Ander\nson.\nTrade, Tenn.: Glenn Wilson.\nLansing: Powell Miller and\nJoseph E. Weaver.\nFleetwood: Dallas A. Williams.\nThose separated from the navy:\nWest Jefferson: Emory N. Lew\nis, Roy Poe.\nLansing: Marvin E. Claycomb.\nCOUNTY GRANGE UNITS\nPLAN IMPROVEMENTS\n1 (Continued from Page 1)\nCrumpler in the near future.\nMasters of the four active units\nin the county are as follows:\nLaurel, Herbert Graybeal; Jef\nfersons, Fred Colvard; Nathan\u2019s\nCreek, W. L. Woodie, Lansing,\nEd Eller.\nFrank Jeeter, of the extension\ndivision, of State College highly\ncomplimented the Ashe Grange\nunits in a broadcast over the\nradio last wek.\nWAR BONDS will guard a\ngainst a post-war depression.\nFAST RELIEF\nFrom Too Frequent Urination,\nBackache, Run-Down Feeling\n\u2014due to irritation of the bladder\ncaused by excess acidity in the urine\nFamous doctor\u2019s discovery acts on the\nkidneys and helps keep you from getting\nup nights!\nAre y.ou suffering unnecessary discom\nfort and distress from ba'ckoche, burning\nurine, frequent desire to pass water?\nGetting up often at night? These symp\ntoms may be caused by bladder irritation\ndue to excess acid in the urine. Then try\nthat famous doctor\u2019s discovery DR.\nKILMER\u2019S SWAMP ROOT.\nFamous for many years. Swamp Root is\nm carefully blended combination of herbs,\nroots, balsam aad other natural ingre\ndients. There\u2019s absolutely nothing harsh\nor habit-forming in this scientific prepara\ntion. Just good ingredients that quickly\nact on the kidneys to increase the. flow of\nurine and relieve bladder irritation and\nits uncomfortable, distressing symptoms.\nYou\u2019ll say its marvelous effect is won\nderful!\nSend for free, prepaid sample TODAY!\nLike thousands of others you\u2019ll be glad\nthat you did. Send name and address to\nDepartment F, Kilmer Co., Inc. Box\n1255, Stamford, Conn. Offer limited. Send\nat one*. All druggists sell Swamp Root.\nTHE SKYLAND POST, WEST JEFFERSON. N. C.\nGilmer Bledsoe\nIs On Way Home\nPearl Harbor, T .H.\u2014Gilmer L.\nBledsoe, Ph. M. 2-C, USNR, the\nhusband of Mrs. Mildred P. Bled\nsoe, of Todd, is on his way home.\nBledsoe is one of 3,730 high\npoint veterans whom the \u201cMagic\nCarpet\u201d is bringing back to the\nStates aboard the USS Saratoga.\nThe USS Saratoga\u2014one of more\nthan 250 carriers, battleships,\ncruisers, and attack transports in\nthe Navy\u2019s famed \u201cMagic Carpet\u201d\nfleet\u2014left Pearl Harbor, Wed\nnesday, November 14, and is\nscheduled to\u2019 arrive in San Fran\ncisco about Sunday, November 18.\nPassengers will go directly to\nthe Separation Centers nearest\ntheir homes to complete the for\nmalities of obtaining their dis\ncharges before returning to civ\nilian life.\nIL B. Ham, Husk U\np\nStore jf 1\nSMITH\nWhile there are still some shortages in many lines, we are pleased to announce\nthat we have an unusually good selection of really beautiful Christmas gifts. Our\nstock in some departments cannot be rep laced, and for this reason, we ask that you w/>' W\nshop early. Make your selection now and use our LAY-A WAY PLAN. W\n(111 Here Are Only A Few Os Our\nSuggestions:\nGIVE PERFUME OR TOILET WATER THE GIFT BS\u00aeB\u00abr I\u2019?\nFOR her. I\nWe have a wide selection of brands\u2014Cara Nome I G3I tf! BI W.\nm and man others p riced from 59c 5 #0 w\nI Toilet Sets *1.98 